<soapenv:Envelope xmlns:soapenv="http://schemas.xmlsoap.org/soap/envelope/" xmlns:sec="http://schemas.xmlsoap.org/ws/2002/12/secext" xmlns:mes="http://www.ebxml.org/namespaces/messageHeader" xmlns:ns="http://webservices.sabre.com/sabreXML/2011/10">
   <soapenv:Header>
      <sec:Security><sec:BinarySecurityToken>$SWS_BinarySecurityToken$</sec:BinarySecurityToken></sec:Security>
      <mes:MessageHeader mes:version="1.0" mes:id="79979892">
         <mes:From>
            <!--1 or more repetitions:-->
            <mes:PartyId>PSSIntegration.aa.com</mes:PartyId>
         </mes:From>
         <mes:To>
            <!--1 or more repetitions:-->
            <mes:PartyId>pm.dev.esoa.qcorpaa.aa.com</mes:PartyId>
         </mes:To>
         <mes:CPAId>AAO</mes:CPAId>
         <mes:ConversationId>iDEV Direct Managed</mes:ConversationId>
         <mes:Service>QueuePlaceLLSRQ</mes:Service>
         <mes:Action>QueuePlaceLLSRQ</mes:Action>
         <mes:MessageData>
            <mes:MessageId>RPA_RIPA_$RequestID$</mes:MessageId>
            <mes:Timestamp>$m-date-string$</mes:Timestamp>
         </mes:MessageData>
      </mes:MessageHeader>
   </soapenv:Header>
   <soapenv:Body>
      <ns:QueuePlaceRQ Version="2.0.4" ReturnHostCommand="true">
         <ns:QueueInfo>
            <ns:QueueIdentifier PrefatoryInstructionCode="$vPrefactoryInstructionCode$" PseudoCityCode="$vPseudoCityCode$" Number="$vQueueNumber$"/>
         </ns:QueueInfo>
      </ns:QueuePlaceRQ>
   </soapenv:Body>
</soapenv:Envelope>
QueuePlace response includes $lstMessage.LegacyAutomation:getLegacyIndexValue($Loop-Counter-2.LegacyAutomation:getDecrementedNumber$)$, running ignore transaction.
QueuePlace response includes $lstMessage.LegacyAutomation:getLegacyIndexValue($Loop-Counter-2.LegacyAutomation:getDecrementedNumber$)$, running switch to duty five action.
QueuePlace response includes $lstMessage.LegacyAutomation:getLegacyIndexValue($Loop-Counter-2.LegacyAutomation:getDecrementedNumber$)$, running switch to duty zero action.
QueuePlace response includes $lstMessage.LegacyAutomation:getLegacyIndexValue($Loop-Counter-2.LegacyAutomation:getDecrementedNumber$)$, running QP again.
QueuePlace response includes $lstMessage.LegacyAutomation:getLegacyIndexValue($Loop-Counter-2.LegacyAutomation:getDecrementedNumber$)$, running cancel not authorized action.
QueuePlace response includes $lstMessage.LegacyAutomation:getLegacyIndexValue($Loop-Counter-2.LegacyAutomation:getDecrementedNumber$)$, running AE¥OVR action.

variables.name: ENV
variables.description:
Specify which environment you want to run (Dev: TSTS, Stage: CERT, Production: RES).
Pass $ENV$ from taskbot.

variables.name: Response_Error
variables.description: The error message, if service call was unsuccessful.

variables.name: SWS_BinarySecurityToken
variables.description:
This variable holds the security token used to access SWS. Default value is null; metabot will create one when it is first called.
The same variable should be used for all tasks/subtasks in a process.

variables.name: logFolder
variables.description:
Path to the folder containing the log file.
Pass $Path_Logs$ from taskbot.

variables.name: logFile
variables.description:
File where Sabre actions will be logged.
Pass $vInfoLogFile$ from taskbot.

variables.name: vPNRLocator
variables.description:
The locator of the PNR you are queue placing.
Default value is 'NOLOCATOR' if no locator is provided.

variables.name: vTextResponse
variables.description: The Sabre response message to the service call.

variables.name: vXMLResponse
variables.description: The full service response in XML format.

variables.name: TaskName
variables.description:
Name of task which is calling SWS metabot.
Pass $Task_Name$ from taskbot.

variables.name: Response_Status
variables.description: Returns SUCCESS if service call is successful; returns WARNING/ERROR/FAIL otherwise.

variables.name: vQueueNumber
variables.description: The queue number where the record is to be placed, e.g. 112

variables.name: SWS_Username
variables.description: Username for Sabre Web Services (e.g. TID, SID, or ZID)
